</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B291B68B9E52FF826DBAFEB53264C683" pageId="5" pageNumber="436" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E52FF826DBAFEB53264C683" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E52FF826DBAFEB53274C6A7" bold="true" box="[199,334,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name derives from Latin 
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E52FF826FD9FEB531C7C6A6" box="[676,765,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">arcanus</emphasis>
[- 
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E52FF826E62FEB53017C6A6" box="[799,813,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E52FF826E38FEB5305DC6A6" box="[837,871,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="436">um</emphasis>
] = arcane, mysterious, due to the strange shape of the male genitalia
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
